## Subcategory [/categories/:id/categories/:subid?include=includes]
Get a single Subcategory object 
+ Parameters
    + id (required, number, `1`) ... Numeric `id` of the Category to perform action with. Has example value.
    + subid (required, number, `2`) ... Numeric `id` of the Subcategory to perform action with. Has example value.
    + includes (optional, string, `'modifier'`) ... `includes` The relations that you want returned as part of the object. Options are: `modifier`, `parent`, or `all`

### Retrieve a Subcategory [GET]
+ Response 200 (application/json)

    + Body

            {
                data: {
                  modified_by: null
                  name: "Newsstand"
                  created_at: "2014-03-25T21:30:42+00:00"
                  updated_at: "2014-03-25T21:30:42+00:00"
                  class: "Category"
                  iab_id: 5 
                  parent_id: :id
                  version: 1
                  modifier: null
                  id: :subid
                }
            }
            
